{"comments":"WorleyNoise - cellular/Voronoi noise configuration.\n\nSteven Worley's cellular noise algorithm (1996), based on distance\nto randomly distributed feature points. Creates organic, cell-like\npatterns found in nature: stone, scales, cells, bubbles.\n\n## Distance Functions\n\nThe noise value at each point is determined by distance to nearby\nfeature points. Different distance metrics create different looks:\n\n- **F1**: Distance to nearest point (cell interiors)\n- **F2**: Distance to second-nearest point (cell boundaries)\n- **F2-F1**: Difference creates sharp cell edges\n- **F1+F2**: Sum creates softer, blob-like cells\n\n## Composition\n\nA molecule composed from Material pillar atoms:\n- NoiseFrequency: cell density (0.0 to finite)\n- NoiseAmplitude: output range (0.0 to 1.0)\n- NoiseSeed: deterministic seed (any Int)\n- DistanceType: F1, F2, F2MinusF1, F1PlusF2\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\n-- Cell interior pattern\ncells = worleyNoise\n  { frequency: noiseFrequency 3.0\n  , amplitude: noiseAmplitude 1.0\n  , seed: noiseSeed 42\n  , distanceType: F1\n  }\n\n-- Sharp cell edges\nedges = worleyNoiseEdges (noiseSeed 42)\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Hydrogen.Schema.Surface.NoiseFrequency\n- Hydrogen.Schema.Surface.NoiseAmplitude\n- Hydrogen.Schema.Surface.NoiseSeed\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[102,7],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[102,3]},"title":"F1"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[103,7],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[103,3]},"title":"F2"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[104,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[104,3]},"title":"F2MinusF1"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[105,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[105,3]},"title":"F1PlusF2"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[106,7],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[106,3]},"title":"F3"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","WorleyNoise"],"DistanceType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[108,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[108,1]},"title":"eqDistanceType"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","WorleyNoise"],"DistanceType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[109,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[109,1]},"title":"ordDistanceType"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","WorleyNoise"],"DistanceType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[116,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/WorleyNoise.purs","start":[111,1]},"title":"showDistanceType"}],"comments":"Distance function type for Worley noise.\n\nDetermines how the noise value is calculated from feature point distances.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[106,7],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surfa